Not all direct sales and network marketing companies are created equal! 

When you are considering a company to partner with, there are many factors you should consider.

One is the percentage of revenue that is invested in the compensation program.

At Park Lane Jewelry, .72 of every dollar is invested into our comp plan. The average in the industry is around .35 of every dollar! 

What does this mean? Park Lane offers an incredibly lucrative compensation package to attract top talent in the profession. 

How can Park Lane pay so much more? 67 years in business has created a cash rich, debt free company with zero investors. The owners have chosen for over 6 decades to invest in what matters most, people! And it’s paid off hugely! 

If you have experience in our industry, it’s smart to get educated on what’s out there. 
Knowledge is power and I’m eternally grateful that 5 years ago I said “YES” to learning more! That decision to walk through a door to learn more not only changed my life, but has changed thousands of others!

Have you ever had a job (like actual job where you are an employee) and we’re demoted? 

I personally have not BUT if I had, I can only imagine it would be very damaging to my confidence and belief in myself! 

Well, in many network marketing and social selling companies, if you do not qualify by hitting certain rank levels for a certain time frame, you lose your title or career rank and essentially are demoted. This can have a domino effect and have a negative impact on not only psyche but also earnings. 

At Park Lane, people do not lose titles. You earn a title, you are forever at that title and paid at that title weekly unless you decide to promote to the next level.

This is almost unheard of in my profession, but it’s one of the things that attracted me to Park Lane 5 years ago! 

Park Lane has the philosophy that we are in the empowerment business! How would demoting someone empower them? It actually does the opposite and for that reason, Park Lane doesn’t do it! 

I spent my first 10 years in the industry building a lot of people back that felt beat down when they lost their titles! I’m eternally grateful I haven’t had to have this conversation the last 5! And guess what happens  when people don’t lose their titles and are paid at their career ranks weekly? They are more empowered, more productive and more driven as a result! 

Drop A ❤️ if you find this info interesting! 

#directselling #socialselling #networkmarketingleader #workfromhome  #jewelrybusiness #parklanejewelry

Growing up, teachers would always tell me that Macey is a ray of sunshine! ☀️

For those of you with young kids…I could not recommend study abroad more! I loved it and so does she! It’s a life changer for sure! 🫶🏼🇪🇸🌞

Spain is a country that is near and dear to my heart! It’s where I studied abroad as a senior in college!! It’s where I truly mastered the Spanish language (there was a day I considered myself fluent. I’m rusty now but immersion back in the language definitely helps you get it back quickly). It’s where I fell in true love with the Spanish culture and helped me build an even greater appreciation for the Cuban culture our mother comes from. It’s also where I grew the most as a person! I had to REALLY stretch myself! I did get homesick! I desperately missed @jonmefferd (my boyfriend at the time). I really missed my family (I remember being away for some big events that were happening in my sister’ lives). We didn’t have cell phones. I walked to the Cortes Ingles every Sunday where they had a phone station and would call and talk to my parents for about 5-10 min. I’d get to do the same with Jonathan but less often…maybe every 2-3 weeks. Calling the US was crazy expensive! I remember it costing about $20 for that weekly call with my parents. 

It was while I was away I developed a love of writing! I wrote several letters weekly on the thinnest of paper (because it was less to mail) to feel connected with those I was missing the most. I journaled almost daily…I need to pull that journal out when I get home! It’s another area of my life where I really had to get out of my comfort zone! After spending all my life on a very small town, then going away to college only an hour away, THIS was scary land for me! But I did it anyway! Even through some of the hard of it (having to have an emergency appendectomy a week after arriving being one of them), my courage and bravery muscles grew and strengthened! 

One of the greatest lessons I learned during that time is to go big AND bold as often as you can! Getting uncomfortable was exactly what I needed! Changing the scenery was what helped me see things through a different lense! Immersing myself at the University of Madrid with ALL my classes in Spanish, and going “all in” helped me grow not only as a student but also as a human being! I got really good at listening (cont in comments).

¡Viva España! 🇪🇸💃🫶🏼

Do you love to wear earrings but often stick to the basics? If so, it's time to try some statement earrings! Not only will they enhance your outfits, but they also have many benefits. Let’s explore the advantages of wearing statement earrings.

This morning we made a stop in Hershey, Pennsylvania for breakfast and a quick tour of the Hershey Museum. 

What an adorable town! I’m incredibly impressed and I’ve personally never seen an amusement park laced through the center of town like that! 

Biggest surprise…discovering that Hershey made a big impact in Cuba, our mother’s home country, from 1916-1946. I loved learning about how Mr. Hershey went into that country and built a railroad, mill and town, Central Hershey, so that he could control his sugar supply, the key ingredient in his chocolate.

His influence forever changed that community and while he ultimately  had to sell due to political unrest and before Fidel Castro took over, his legacy has impacted future generations! 

Super cute town  that you should check out if you are ever in the area! 

For all my Pennsylvania friends…I wish SO badly we had more time and I could have seen you all! 🍫🤎

The direct selling/network marketing profession can change your life! I don’t say this to be dramatic, I say it because it’s a fact and I’ve witnessed and experienced it over and over again! 

With that being said, having had 2 experiences with 2 companies, the company you build with matters. Not all companies are created equal and if you choose to work to change your life (or the lives of others), make sure you choose a company that sets you up for success. If you aren’t sure what you should look for, message me and I’m happy to share more with you on what matters.

With that being said, here are some pieces of advice for changing your life through network marketing:

1. Education is Key: Make sure to truly understand the product or service you're marketing. The more you know, the better you can promote it. Continual learning is important in this industry. Attend virtual seminars and training, read books, and keep up to date with the latest trends. I love the jewelry category because it’s simple & fun and very easy for others to learn! 

2. Set Goals: Setting clear, detailed goals is an integral part of succeeding in any business, but particularly in network marketing. Make sure your goals are measurable, achievable, realistic, and have a deadline. We are currently talking with our team about November goals and we’ve not yet wrapped up October.

3. Building a Network: Focus on creating solid relationships. Direct selling starts with your first sale, but building long-term relationships with clients or members of your team is key.

4. Persistence: Rejections are a part of any sales industry. Learn from your losses but don't dwell on them. Keep pushing forward with positivity and resilience.

5. Help Others: Scaling your business is tied to the success of your team. Assisting your team members helps you in that their success also results in your success. So, be willing to mentor, guide, and support your team members.

Remember, success in direct selling doesn't come overnight. It takes time, patience, and a lot of hard work. But with persistence and the right mindset, you can significantly change your life through this amazing business model. 🌟🌟🌟

In this month of gratitude, I want to share my suggestions on how as a leader, you can SHOW your gratitude with your teams! I’m a big believer that actions speak much louder than words and here are my top tips. 

1. Express Gratitude Regularly: Don't wait for a special occasion to express gratitude. Make a habit of frequently letting your team know that you appreciate their hard work and dedication.

2. Be Specific: When you express gratitude, be as specific as possible. Instead of simply saying "good job," articulate exactly what the person did well. This shows that you're paying attention and that you value their specific contributions.

3. Public Recognition: Recognize their contributions during team meetings/zooms, in team Facebook groups, etc. Praise and acknowledgment in front of colleagues can be a strong motivator.

4. Personalize Your Appreciation: Get to know your team and personalize your gratitude. Some may appreciate public recognition, while others may prefer a private text or conversation. 

5. Encourage Peer Recognition: Encourage team members to acknowledge and appreciate each other’s work. This can foster a culture of gratitude and enhance team cohesion.

6. Lead by Example: Show that gratitude is an important part of your company culture by modelling it yourself.

7. Give Tangible Rewards: While a simple thank you goes a long way, tangible rewards like a fun incentive/treat or even a hand written note can also show your gratitude and go a really long way.

8. Provide Opportunities for Growth: Providing opportunities for supporting advancement/promoting and professional development shows your team that you appreciate them and are invested in their success.

9. Listen: Show your gratitude by listening to their ideas and concerns. This demonstrates that you value and appreciate their perspectives.

10. Remember Important Dates: Remembering birthdays or work anniversaries can go a long way in making someone feel appreciated and valued.

This April it will be 6 years that I decided to take a sharp right turn and form a new partnership with Park Lane Jewelry! 

I was INCREDIBLY excited to help them build a NEW generation and it’s truly mind blowing to see the impact we have made together since arriving!!

It’s funny..when I arrived, I thought I knew it ALL! 🤣🤣

Lesson learned…you NEVER stop learning and when I look at the growth I’ve personally experienced the last near 6 years, there are moments I don’t even see the same leader that arrived here! 

Tonight I had the honor of speaking at our kick off to our Sparkle Conference and it was the first time for me to train on our Leadership night! 

I talked about what Visionary Leadership looks like and how to set yourself apart from the rest of the pack by setting transformative goals vs routine goals! 

Routine goals might move the needle a bit in your business, but they are not going to transform your business and definitely not your life! 

We all have been taught to play it safe! I play it safe on the ski slopes and when on a bicycle! I have ZERO desire for wanting to go faster! Literally ZERO!

But if I wanted to improve my skiing or cycling game, I’d have to increase my goals and up my game! 

Same goes for your business! Want more? It’s time to elevate your goals!

Are you a trip earner? The first time you earn the trip…working for that trip likely transformed your business! The 5th trip you earned, that has now become a routine goal!  It’s important, you’ve proven you can do it, it’s NOT going to transform your business! 

See the difference? 

Want MORE in 2024? It’s time to level up, create a vision that others want to be a part of and set a transformative goal that will help you get closer to transforming your business and your life!
